tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
context: Pregnancy Check Up,High-Risk Pregnancy Care,Fertility Treatment,
review: Dr. Reena Khandelwal is one of the most professional and friendly doctor I have met.she is very pretty. I visited to Khandelwal clinic for my high risk pregnancy case  . I was suffering with depression as well . Dr Reena gave *** **** ********** *** counseling support with her beautiful positive smile. I really appreciate to Dr. Reena more than I could possibly explain. She is available on phone  for 24*7  for her pateints. I strongly recommend Dr .Reena for high risk pregnancy and infertility treatment.

A Perfect Doctor! In todays life it is very difficult to find a doctor who understands your problems and provides the right solution . Reena mam has been a blessing in disguise and just made my pregnancy a very comfortable experience... I highly appreciate the way she was always available and gave the right advise everytime I faced any issue. Her smiling face and positive attitude just makes a person so much more comfortable.. I cant thank her enough for all the support and encouragement throughout my pregnancy period. Highly recommend her.

It was a great experience for us, now more than 9 months associated medically with the doctor. We consulted her for my wife's pregnancy , rather even before we knew that my wife was pregnant. She was through out very patient, helpful, best at what she does, punctual ,************** ******** * always available for her patients and resourceful. She is not at all pessimistic, not at all kind of doctor who will scare u even for a day while making sure that the utmost care and precautions are being taken. We both were working , travelled internationally as well without being too stressed out.Time flew and we are blessed with a baby boy. We will like to recommend Dr Reena Khandelwal to everyone who will like to enjoy the phase rather than taking it as a burden!!

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: Dr.Reena was really warm and listened to all my issues with patience, very gregarious in nature and made sure I was comfortable throughout the time I was in the clinic ,I consulted her for my ongoing PCOS, she explained the issue and solutions with in-depth understanding and articulated it in a way which was easy for us to comprehend, not only did she suggested intervention through medicines she advised easily adaptable lifestyle changes to be able to curb the issue in a holistic way, overall I was really satisfied with my appointment, for an absolutely non judgemental and safe experience I’d suggest her name for sure.

My home test was positive seeking doctor consultation , i booked an appointment.First She came late , then  in haste without counseling me  she called **** ****** doctor to come down for ultrasound,  not even bothering to let her patient   know y it is  required needlesstosay forget about asking me the details or  letting  me comfortable . On me hesitating for the ultrasound,  i guess then she realsied abt my disagreemnt with her then she started narrating the pregnancy procedure and symptoms and rest other basic knowledge, without even bothering what all symptoms I might be facing . here I was suppose to assume ,yes if i my facing any issues it is a symptom of pregnancy , then on giving me a flag of trust the doc she accompanied me to ultrasound room and got the thing done then the fellow doc said it too early to say but  the sack is formed you are 5 week pregnant and asked me  come after 10 days,  rest is ok . I asked if i can share the news with family ** * *** **** **  ********  ********* * no as u r thyroid patient don't  as any thing may happen * *** *** ******* ** ** ******** * *** ***** ** * *** *** ** ******* .aftet this I thought of meeting the doc with the reports only to find that she has left .
******** ***********  
if we talk abt charges the entire procedure costed me around 4.5k ( consultancy +ultrasound) . I would have not regretted if the doc was satisfactory as I was expecting the high charges in th hospital like  Appolo cradle .

tags: Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: We went last month on monday 22nd oct for my first pregnancy check up in my 8-9 week and they did test for 8500 and said ul get ur report in mail by thursday 25th which i didnt get. I called even on Saturday/Sunday that i haven't received but no one answered. So i forgot n called again on Thursday at the clinic and Doc both thy said give us 10 mins we will call you back. But someone called and took the email id which i even mentioned when the test were done and sent the mail didnt evn call or mail the report is fine or not. Unacceptable behavior from all the staff.
reply_text:
We are sorry if we could not satisfy you .Will  talk to my staff and make sure such situation does not occur again 
Sorry for the inconvenience caused to you 
Regards 
Dr Reena

review: *** ***** ** ** ********* ****** She took the time to explain every procedure she was doing.Dr. Reena was very supportive, and thorough when explaining the process. She is a professional and has a naturally lovely personality. I would highly recommend Dr. Reena to everyone. *** ** *** **** ***** * **** **** ****

it has been nice always , we are associated to Dr Reena since 2006 and  we have recommended number of our near n dear to visit her and they got benefitted too , Now this  visit transformed into great bonding 

Let her stay blessed.
Thanks 
Harikesh Mishra & Kiran MIshra with our two blessed kid ( Arnav & Aarohi)

Very friendly. It was our first visit regarding maternity and people normally feel uncomfortable to ask questions to the doctor or shy to give answer. But she really made the environment so casual that it was kind of no prob for us to ask or tell anything to the doctor. Must say very caring.....
